AVIAN INFLUENZA (35): SOUTH KOREA (SOUTH JEOLLA) LPNAI H7N7, OIE
****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Fri 21 May 2010
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly
disease information 2010; 23(21) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahis/public.php?page=single_report&pop=1&reportid=9287>


Low pathogenic avian influenza (poultry), Korea (Rep. of)
---------------------------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 21 May 2010 from Dr Kiyoon Chang,
CVO & Director, Labelling, Quarantine and Inspection Division, Food
Safety & Consumer Affairs Policy Bureau, MIFAFF (Ministry of Food,
Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries), Gyeonggi-Do, Korea (Rep. of)

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 13 May 2010
Date of first confirmation of the event: 20 May 2010
Report date: 21 May 2010
Date submitted to OIE: 21 May 2010
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 27 Dec 2009
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Low pathogenic avian influenza virus
Serotype: H7N7
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Wolya-myeon, Hampyeong-gun, Cholla-Namdo [Jeollanam-do,
South Jeolla]
Outbreak 2 Bongsan-myeon, Damyang-gun, Cholla-Namdo
Both outbreaks started 13 May 2010

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Birds (Ducks) / 53 300 / **/ 0 / 53 300 / 0
** Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: as part of the avian influenza surveillance
programme, Jeollanam-do Institute of Livestock and Veterinary Science
took samples (faeces, laryngopharyngeal swabs, and blood) from the
farms on 13 May 2010. Haemagglutination test results were positive on
18 May 2010. The National Veterinary Research and Quarantine Service
(NVRQS) found avian influenza antigen (H7) by PCR on 20 May 2010 and
confirmed it as low pathogenic avian influenza virus (H7N7) by gene
sequencing on 21 May 2010.
The poultry in the farms were culled as a precautionary measure and
disinfection is being implemented on 21 May 2010.

Note by the OIE Animal Health Information Department: H5 and H7 avian
influenza in its low pathogenic form in poultry is a notifiable
disease as per Chapter 10.4. on avian influenza of the Terrestrial
Animal Health Code (2009).

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out; quarantine; movement control inside
the country; zoning; disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s); vaccination prohibited; no treatment of
affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Interactive maps of South Korea can be seen at notification URL
above and the HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at
<http://healthmap.org/r/01iV>.

The 3 previous LPAI outbreaks in S Korea, reported during 2009, were
the following:
Species / serotype / start date / confirmation date / OIE notification date
1. Birds (ducks) / H5N2 / 29 Dec 2008 / 29 Dec 2008 / 2 Jan 2009
2. Birds (ducks) / H7N2 / 26 Nov 2009 / 13 Dec 2009 / 13 Dec 2009
3. Birds (ducks) / H5N2 / 7 Dec 2009 / 25 Dec 2009 / 28 Dec 2009

In all outbreaks, stamping out policy was applied.- Mod.AS]
